default24.
default 
defaultThe industry has responded positively.
default 
defaultAs detailed in our
default De
defaultcember 2012 report into passenger information,
default 
defaultmany station staff now have smart phones with access to real-time data, while ticket office staff have better access to up to date information.
default 
defaultWhile this still requires stress-testing in a live situation, th
defaulte level and quality of information for passengers at stations, online and through social media has and continues to improve across the industry.
default 
default 
defaultThe indus
defaulttry 
defaultupdate their plans annually 
defaultand 
defaultto take into account developments in technology, changes to 
defaultpassenger needs and lessons learnt in the light of experience. ORR
default 
defaultengages with industry and 
defaultmonitors
default 
defaultperformance to ensure that all parties fulfil their obligations and in 2014 we intend to review the current code to identify whether further improvements 
defaultare required.
default 
defaultIn addition, the £100
defaultm
default fund for station improvements in 2014-19 could be used to improve passenger information systems, however this would need to be considered against competing us
defaultes
default for the fund and decided under the governance procedures.
default&#xa0;
default25.
default 
defaultDuring times of severe weather, passengers often have to make sophisticated travel decisions, taking into consideration the full range of travel modes available to the
defaultm –
default 
defaultfor example, rail, road, bus, car or
default 
defaultworking
default from home. While the availability and quality of rail information has improved, the passenger experience
default, it
default could be 
defaultfurther 
defaultimproved by 
defaultproviding 
defaulteasier access to local and regional cross-modal transport information. This would enable customers to compr
defaultehensively plan their journey with
default the
default confidence that they have information about all of the travel options open to them. The 
defaultDepartment for Transport
default has set out its view on the value of cross-modal information in the
defaultir
default recent 
defaultstrategy; 
default“
defaultDoor to Door – a
default strategy for improving sustainable transport.”
default 
defaultWe believe that access to cross-modal transport information is particularly important in times of service disruption and are actively encouraging the industry to continue to make data available to third-part
defaulty data developers who could develop software applications to provide this functionality
default to the travelling public
